Authors: Vishal Sinha, Ayush Chanda, Sahil Kulkarni, Oliver Engles, Brandon Hernandez, Shreshth Sharma, Rick Sharma

Version: Alpha

Date: April 20, 2026

General Instructions: 
	
	How to play: 
		1. The game is played on a 10x8 board (files A-J, ranks 1-8)
		
		2. Enter moves in the format: "A2 A3" (start position, then the end position)
		The start position has the file position, while the end position has the rank position
			
		3. The player with the white pieces move first, then the player with the black player goes. The order is alternate.
		
		4. Pieces are displayed as: wR (white rook), bP (black pawn), etc. The initial letter is lowercase and describes the color side the piece is in.
		The second letter is the uppercase letter and describes the piece of each side.

		5. The game ends when a king is in checkmate. The player doing the checkmate wins the game
	
	Pieces:
		- P = Pawn/Ant, R = Rook, N = Knight, B = Bishop
		- Q = Queen, K = King, A = Anteater
		- w = white, b = black

	Special Moves:
		- Anteating: Anteater can chain eat adjacent enemy pawns in one move. 
		- Pawn Promotion: Pawns can move 2 squares from starting position
		- Castling and en passant are explained in the user manual and are supported in our alpha version
	
	Quit: The user can quit the game anytime.

	Install: Refer to INSTALL for installing instructions

		
